l is evident in the quality of academic enrichment programs  offering opportunities for cadets to challenge themselves beyond the classroom  undergraduate research  international programs  Institute Honors  service learning  and graduate school partnerships allow cadets to engage in rigorous academic paths that often exceed expectations  Undergraduate Research A robust undergraduate research program links cadets and professors in the exploration of open ended research questions  The research culminates in a capstone experience  The Summer Undergraduate Research Institute is an intense ten week program in which cadets pursue their research under the guidance of a faculty mentor  Research is presented annually at the VMI Undergraduate Research Symposium or at other regional or national conferences  More about Undergraduate Research at VMI International Programs Preparing young men and women for successful service in a world of rapidly integrating cultures and interdependent economies is an inherent component of VMI s mission  Programs include international military academy exchange programs  semester abroad programs  summer abroad programs  international internships  and cultural exchanges and study tours  More about International Programs Institute Honors Established for students who achieve at high levels  the program includes honors courses  with enrollment limited to 12  special forums on current events  and a capstone senior honors project or thesis  Graduating with Institute Honors is the highest academic achievement at VMI  These cadets may also be recognized via national awards such as the Rhodes  Marshall  and Gates scholarships  VMI has had 11 Rhodes scholars to date  More about Institute Honors   Service Learning The VMI experience emphasizes the value of service by preparing cadets to become citizen soldiers who will serve their country and communities  To that end  VMI s Community Outreach and Renewal Experience   the CORE initiative   offers opportunities to learn about service at the local  national  and international levels  Classroom experiences and hands on participation in community projects give cadets an awareness of the importance of service in the lives of citizen soldiers  More about Service Learning Institute Writing Program The Institute Writing Program seeks to equip cadets for both academic success and participation in the full range of rhetorical occasions they will encounter in their lives as citizens and professionals  To ensure the development of strong written communication abilities  the program s curriculum provides sequential  sustained writing instruction and support throughout cadets  academic careers at VMI  More about the Institute Writing Program Academics Majors   Minors Areas of Study Course Catalog Enrichment Programs Institute Honors International Programs Undergraduate Research Service Learning Institute Writing Services   Support Summer Programs Research at VMI Scholarships Office of the Dean Dean s Office P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office Virginia Military Institute 210 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450  Academics Majors   Minors Areas of Study Course Catalog Enrichment Programs Institute Honors International Programs Undergraduate Research Service Learning Institute Writing Services   Support Summer Programs Research at VMI Scholarships Office of the Dean Dean s Office P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office Virginia Military Institute 210 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Academics Majors   Minors Areas of Study Course Catalog Enrichment Programs Institute Honors International Programs Undergraduate Research Service Learning Institute Writing Services   Support Summer Programs Research at VMI Scholarships Office of the Dean Academics Academics Majors   Minors Majors   Minors Areas of Study Areas of Study Course Catalog Course Catalog Enrichment Programs Institute Honors International Programs Undergraduate Research Service Learning Institute Writing Enrichment